main event: An observer reported seeing a bullet-shaped object that disappeared toward the north on October 12, 1966.
interesting points: The object had a yellowish inside area changing to a reddish hue on the edges., No exhaust or propulsion was observed during the sighting., The object was estimated to be similar to a meteor but with an unusual appearance., The sighting lasted only a few seconds, making it difficult for the observer to give a complete description., The case was concluded as an 'astro (meteor)' by investigators.
